Add an in-memory key-value store with TTL (Time-To-Live) support and LRU (Least Recently Used) eviction. Create `src/kvstore.js` with the following:

1) `createKVStore(options)` - factory function. Options:
   - `maxSize` (number, default Infinity) - max number of entries before LRU eviction
   - `defaultTTL` (number ms, default 0 = no expiry) - default TTL for all entries
   - `onEvict(key, value)` - optional callback when an entry is evicted (LRU or TTL)

2) Returns an object with:
   - `set(key, value, ttl?)` - store a value; ttl (ms) overrides defaultTTL for this entry
   - `get(key)` - retrieve a value, returns undefined if missing or expired; accessing a key makes it most-recently-used
   - `has(key)` - returns true if key exists and is not expired
   - `delete(key)` - remove a key; returns true if it existed
   - `clear()` - remove all entries
   - `size()` - returns number of non-expired entries
   - `keys()` - returns array of non-expired keys
   - `values()` - returns array of non-expired values
   - `entries()` - returns array of [key, value] pairs for non-expired entries
   - `ttl(key)` - returns milliseconds until expiry (or Infinity if no TTL), undefined if missing
   - `getStats()` - returns `{ hits, misses, evictions, size }`

3) LRU eviction: when maxSize is exceeded, evict the least recently used entry.

4) TTL enforcement: expired entries are lazily removed on access and eagerly via a periodic sweep every 30 seconds.

5) Write tests in `tests/kvstore.test.js` covering: basic get/set, TTL expiry, LRU eviction, has/delete/clear, size/keys/values/entries, stats tracking, and onEvict callback.

6) Export `createKVStore` from `src/index.js`.
